  <front>
   <head>VERSES said to be fixed on the Gate of the LOUVRE at PARIS. 1751.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">OUR fathers' victims the two Henries see,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">This to  that to</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Louis, in thee again the tyrants live;</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Dread, lest our deep despair those scenes revive.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">nor yet a  denies,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The  a  nor the  a</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
